---
import ContentLayout from '@/layouts/content-layout.astro'
---

<ContentLayout
	title="KOL Platform Rebuild — Ilzam"
	description="Led the technical rebuild of a KOL management platform from 85% to 99% uptime, serving 5,000+ daily active users. Jakarta, Indonesia."
>
	<a href="/work" class="text-sm text-muted-foreground hover:text-foreground">&larr; All work</a>

	<div class="mt-6 flex items-center justify-between">
		<span class="rounded-sm bg-muted px-2 py-0.5 text-xs font-medium uppercase">Platform Rebuild</span>
		<span class="text-sm text-muted-foreground">Jakarta, Indonesia / 2024</span>
	</div>

	<h1 class="mt-4 text-4xl font-light leading-tight tracking-tight md:text-5xl">
		KOL Platform Rebuild
	</h1>
	<p class="mt-2 text-lg text-muted-foreground">
		85% to 99% uptime. 5,000+ users. One team.
	</p>

	<div class="mt-4 flex flex-wrap gap-1.5">
		{["Full-stack rebuild", "Team lead"].map((tech) => (
			<span class="rounded-full border px-2.5 py-0.5 text-xs">{tech}</span>
		))}
	</div>

	<section class="mt-12">
		<h2 class="text-xl font-semibold">The Challenge</h2>
		<p class="mt-3 leading-relaxed text-muted-foreground">
			A KOL (Key Opinion Leader) management platform in Jakarta was struggling with reliability. Uptime was hovering around 85% — unacceptable for a system serving 5,000+ daily active users. The codebase had accumulated significant technical debt, and the architecture couldn't handle the load.
		</p>
	</section>

	<section class="mt-10">
		<h2 class="text-xl font-semibold">The Approach</h2>
		<p class="mt-3 leading-relaxed text-muted-foreground">
			I led the technical rebuild from the ground up. Instead of patching the existing system, we identified the core failure points — database bottlenecks, missing error handling, no monitoring — and rebuilt with proper architecture. I led a team of developers through the entire process.
		</p>
		<p class="mt-3 leading-relaxed text-muted-foreground">
			The focus was on reliability first, features second. We introduced proper logging, monitoring, and alerting before adding any new functionality.
		</p>
	</section>

	<section class="mt-10">
		<h2 class="text-xl font-semibold">Key Decisions</h2>
		<ul class="mt-3 space-y-3 text-muted-foreground">
			<li class="leading-relaxed">
				<span class="font-medium text-foreground">Full rebuild over incremental fixes.</span>
				The technical debt was deep enough that patching would take longer than rebuilding. When the architecture itself is the problem, you fix the architecture.
			</li>
			<li class="leading-relaxed">
				<span class="font-medium text-foreground">Reliability metrics before feature work.</span>
				We set up monitoring and defined uptime SLAs before writing any feature code. You can't improve what you don't measure.
			</li>
			<li class="leading-relaxed">
				<span class="font-medium text-foreground">Team leadership, not solo hero work.</span>
				This was too large for one person. I brought in developers I trusted, set up clear processes, and led the team through a structured rebuild.
			</li>
		</ul>
	</section>

	<section class="mt-10">
		<h2 class="text-xl font-semibold">The Result</h2>
		<p class="mt-3 leading-relaxed text-muted-foreground">
			Uptime went from 85% to 99%. The platform now serves 5,000+ daily active users reliably. The new architecture is maintainable, monitored, and ready to scale. The team I built continues to maintain and extend the system.
		</p>
	</section>

	<section class="mt-12 border-t pt-8">
		<h3 class="text-sm font-medium uppercase tracking-wider text-muted-foreground">Related Notes</h3>
		<ul class="mt-3 space-y-2">
			<li><a href="/notes/when-to-rewrite-vs-refactor" class="text-sm underline underline-offset-4 hover:text-foreground">When to Rewrite vs Refactor</a></li>
			<li><a href="/notes/when-to-hire-fractional-cto" class="text-sm underline underline-offset-4 hover:text-foreground">When to Hire a Fractional CTO</a></li>
		</ul>
	</section>

	<section class="mt-10 rounded-lg bg-muted/50 p-6 text-center">
		<p class="font-medium">Dealing with a platform that's falling apart?</p>
		<p class="mt-1 text-sm text-muted-foreground">
			I've been through this exact situation. Let's talk about your options.
		</p>
		<a
			href="https://cal.com/ilzam/advisory"
			target="_blank"
			rel="noopener noreferrer"
			class="mt-4 inline-block rounded-full bg-foreground px-5 py-2 text-sm font-medium text-background transition-opacity hover:opacity-90"
		>
			Book an Advisory Session
		</a>
	</section>
</ContentLayout>
